President Obama has announced the appointment of Michael R. Bromwich to lead the efforts in reforming the regulation and oversight of offshore oil drilling. Bromwich will be responsible for reforming the Minerals Management Service (MMS) and developing a new oversight structure that prioritizes environmental and safety regulation. He will also oversee the reorganization of the MMS to eliminate conflicts of interest in oil industry oversight. Bromwich is a former Assistant U.S. Attorney and Justice Department Inspector General, known for his work in reforming broken agencies. His appointment is part of the Interior Department's ongoing reforms in response to the BP Deepwater Horizon Oil Spill.